Origin

The Xandarians are a peaceful humanoid race from the planet Xandar in the Andromeda Galaxy. They are the creators of the Xandarian Worldmind - the keeper of the knowledge and power of the entire race. Most importantly, the Worldmind is the keeper of the Nova Force, a cosmic power used to create the Nova Corps. The Nova Corps are intergalactic peace-keepers and a force for good.

Xandar was destroyed by the Luphomoids and thanks to Uatu the Watcher the culture was able to rebuild their society in massive spheres interconnected to one another. The Xandarian-Skrull War again threathened to population, but it was the space pirate Nebula who would eventually kill all but a few Xandarians.

Thanks to Richard Rider the Worldmind was rebooted and Xandar once again made habitable. Slowly, the Xandarians were cloned and Xandar began to return to its former glory.

Xandar would meet its final destruction at the beginning of the Annihilation War.

deck: Peaceful race with cosmic bad luck. Created Beta Ray Bill for their protection.
description:
Origin

A peaceful race, the planet of Korbin was destroyed by Surtur. They soon found a new planet and dubbed it New Korbin. They chose to create a protector for their people. Thier first attempt was biomechanical creation called Alpha Ray who soon grew beyond their control and was placed in stasis.

On the next attempt, they used cybernetics to create Beta Ray Bill, one who would be worthy of Thor's hammer Mjolnir and even receive an enchanded mallet of his own. Along with the sentient ship Skuttlebutt, they discovered a suitable world they dubbed New Korbin.

Many Korbinites were enslaved and killed in the Cauldron of Coversion by Sidereus and Lord Votan of the Axi-Tun. New Korbin was eventually consumed by Galactus. Many of the Korbinites were saved within the Meta-Orb. But the evil Asteroth hid herself within the Orb and absorbed the Korbinite's essence to become Omega Ray, leaving Bill the last of his kind.

Bill went on a mission of vengeance against Galactus but ultimately ended up saving the world devourer's life. In return, Galactus was able to gather the faintest hint of Korbinite essence to resurrect a female Korbinite, Ti Asha Ra, so that the Korbinite race might live on.

Other Media

The Korbinites were portrayed in the Silver Surfer Animated Series, although they were called the Whynnm and resided on the planet Harmony. All members of the race had the horse-like apperance of Beta Ray Bill.

They were a Utopian society, but their society was built on the illusion they created in the Dream Weaver. The Silver Surfer convinced them to destroy the device and return to reality, rebuild and protect themselves from the evil Thanos.

deck: Also known as Space Jockeys, the Engineers are an advanced alien race believed to be responsible for the creation of humanity, as well as the monstrous "Aliens" known as Xenomorphs.
description:
Origin

Not much is known about the enigmatic Engineers. All that is known is that the Engineers were incredibly advanced genetic engineers who made the Xenomorphs. It has also been shown that they played an important role in influencing the genetic development of mankind and that without them, the human race might never have become a race at all.

The first known contact between an Engineer and the human race happened in 2093 on LV-223. Four years prior in 2089, Archaeologists Elizabeth Shaw and Charlie Holloway discovered star maps in multiple locations that pointed towards LV-223 as a destination. The Weyland Corporation funded an expedition to LV-223. With the help of an android named David, Peter Weyland awakened the sole Engineer on the planet and attempted to communicate with him/her. The Engineer promptly responded by deciding to massacre the greeting party and attempted to fly one of the ships on the planets to Earth in a plan to either exterminate or mutate the human race. Fortunately and sadly, the crew of the ship Prometheus sacrificed their lives and their ship to disable and ground the alien ship. The Engineer then attempted to kill the sole survivor, Elizabeth Shaw, but fell victim to an abomination that Shaw gave birth via c-section. The abomination impregnated the Engineer who in turn gave birth to a Xenomorph-esque creature that burst out of its chest.

The second appearance of the Engineers in human history happened in 2122 when the crew of the Nostromus intercepted a distress signal that was emanating from LV-426. There, the crew found an Engineer ship. The Engineer piloting the ship was already deceased and cause of death seemed to point towards a grievous chest wound. The cargo of the ship was hundreds, if not thousands, of Xenomorph eggs.

Culture and Attitude of the Engineer Race

It is implied that Engineers are an incredibly proud race that tend to look down on other races to the point that they have no qualms about committing a planet-wide extermination as shown by the actions of the Engineer in the film Prometheus. The written language of the Engineers is noted as being extremely similar to the Mesopotamian cuneiform - so similar in fact that the android David that joined the expedition to LV-223 was able to interpret their language. This striking similarity between the two languages must mean that the Engineers made contact with humans long before 2089, explaining how our modern ancestors knew how to draw multiple star maps in caverns and suggesting that the Engineers may have not always been so aggressive towards the human race if they were willing to give humans the gift of written language. However, they may have also given humans the gift of written language simply as part of some unknown experiment.

Biology

Most Engineers seem to be 7+ feet tall and in tremendous physical condition. How much of this is natural or due to tampering with their own genetics is unknown. Underneath their helmets, they look incredibly human-like and have pale, slightly blue skin. They are able to breath oxygen just like humans, as shown by the supply of oxygen on their ships and the fact that they were able to visit Earth very early on without any negative repercussions or the need of any filtration equipment.

Technology

A majority of Engineer technology seems to be genetically based. Almost all of their technology seem to be bio-engineered as it all appears organic in nature, but it is unknown if it was truly bio-engineered or if it was merely an aesthetic choice by the Engineers.

Relationship with the Xenomorphs

The Engineers are presumably the creators of the Xenomorphs, and based on the almost fossilized appearance of the Engineer found on LV-426 in 2122, created this scourge a long time ago. Evidence seems to suggest that the Engineers created the Xenomorphs as the perfect bio-weapon. It appears that Engineer ship found on LV-426 by the crew of the Nostromus may have been some sort of "bio-bomber" that was on its way to disperse its lethal cargo against an unknown enemy before the Engineer aboard the ship ran into some unknown complications and the ship landed, or crashed, onto LV-426.

name: The Engineers

deck: The rampaging protectors of Earth-8 in the DC Multiverse who fight among themselves as much as they fight villians. They are a pastiche/homage to Marvel's The Avengers.
description:
"For generations, life on Earth-8 passed like it does on our world. Largely uneventful, and when problems did arise, they were handled easily by the world’s large population of super heroes. Until a day finally arrived like no other, and Earth-8’s strongest heroes were forced to unite against a common threat. The Retaliators were born!"

Not quite what you were expecting?

Creation

"Retaliators, ready!"

The Retaliators were created by Grant Morrison during his Final Crisis multiverse epic, and later re-appeared in The Multiversity. The name is a play on The Avengers, Marvel's premier super-hero team. Each member is based on a corresponding Marvel character as they exist on Earth-8.

As with the heroes of earth-0, their adventures are fiction published in another parallel worlds under the Major comics editorial label.

History

Final Crisis

"Retaliators, retreat!"

Briefly seen in Final Crisis, (where they were wrongly described as from earth-6), the Retaliators and other heroes of their world were amidst a civil war instigated by a group of secret invasors shapeshifting aliens. Apparently they overcame those crisis,to return to a happier status quo.

Traditionaly, the Retaliators had been lead by American Crusader, an ages old supersoldier and their membership includes the technological armored Machinehead, the thunderwielder Wundajin, the quick to rage Behemoth, the beauty and deadly Red Dragon, the cosmic powered Major Max, the acuratte bowman Deadeye, the athletic Ladybug and the aerial Kite.

Multiversity

"Retaliators, rampage!"

The Retaliators, (along with the rest of earth-8) were heavily featured in Multiversity as one of the earths attacked by the Gentry, using a brainwashing Nix Uotan as their conduit. The Retaliators had to use all their resources and the help of their world's other teams (G-men and Future Family) to stop the attack from another reality, which include the zombie versions of alternate doppelgangers from the Retaliators themselves. Only with the help of Thunderer (Wundajin's doppelganger) and Aquawoman from earth-11, the Retaliators had a chance to stand against the Gentry attack.

After foil the invasion of the Gentry, Machinehead choose to stay with the extradimensional peacekeeper force to thwart any further attack.

Other versions

The precedent of the Retaliators were the Champions of Angor, a direct answer to Marvel's Squadron Supreme. Another parallel were the Maximums, more closely inspired in the Ultimates. Several concepts of the Champions of Angor are still present in the post Flashpoint earth-8. The superheroes from earth-7 also resemble not only Marvel characters but from other editorials too.
name: Retaliators

deck: Obscure forces from beyond the multiverse.
description:
A menace from beyond the multiverse, the Gentry threatens all the worlds with their corruption.

Capable of twisting the laws of the physics and corrupting reality and its inhabitants, The Gentry are living ideas with no regards towards life. They attacked and destroyed earth-7, leaving Thunderer the lone survivor. Only the intervention of Nix Uotan saved Thunderer, who instead was captured and corrupted by the Gentry and used as their agent, attacking Earths 8 ,20 and 51, and releasing Darkseid into the multiverse. With Earth after Earth being attacked the Gentry grows stronger, and on each world the Gentry attacked using agents to deploy different methods of destruction. As of now, it is unknown if the Gentry is operating alone or if they are the underlings of an even darker power. It has been speculated than each Eldritch abomination-like entity represents a supervillian archetype powered up to Godlike levels.

Until now their registered attacks are:

  • On earth-16, Dame Merciless infected the dreams of the entire world and the mind of Megamorpho, Alexis Luthor and many others.
  • Earth-4 was possibly under the attack of Intellectron, same as earth-33.
  • On earth-5, Demogorgunn, manifested as the plurality of the legion of Sivanas, attacked the heart of all magic, the rock of eternity.
  • Hellmachine directly attacked the House of Heroes.
  • Lord Broken infected the dreams of Overman in earth-10.
